params.name: text
params.description: The copyright text for this album.

params.name: type
params.description: The type of copyright: C = the copyright, P = the sound recording (performance) copyright.

params.name: album_type
params.description: The type of the album: one of 'album', 'single', or 'compilation'.

params.name: artists
params.description: The artists of the album. Each artist object includes a link in href to more detailed information about the artist.

params.name: available_markets
params.description: The markets in which the album is available: ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country codes. Note that an album is considered available in a market when at least 1 of its tracks is available in that market.

params.name: copyrights
params.description: The copyright statements of the album.

params.name: genres
params.description: A list of the genres used to classify the album. For example: 'Prog Rock', 'Post-Grunge'. (If not yet classified, the array is empty.)

params.name: href
params.description: A link to the Web API endpoint providing full details of the album.

params.name: id
params.description: The Spotify ID for the album.

params.name: images
params.description: The cover art for the album in various sizes, widest first.

params.name: name
params.description: The name of the album.

params.name: popularity
params.description: The popularity of the album. The value will be between 0 and 100, with 100 being the most popular. The popularity is calculated from the popularity of the album's individual tracks.

params.name: release_date
params.description: The date the album was first released, for example '1981-12-15'. Depending on the precision, it might be shown as '1981' or '1981-12'.

params.name: release_date_precision
params.description: The precision with which release_date value is known: 'year', 'month', or 'day'.
